---
import AppLayout from "../layouts/AppLayout.astro";
---

<AppLayout
  title="Bore v2 workspace"
  description="Encrypted peer-to-peer file transfer with relay fallback."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Phase 4 -- Relay transfer MVP</p>
      <h2>End-to-end encrypted file transfer through the v2 relay.</h2>
      <p>
        The v2 lane now supports real encrypted file transfers. Select a file,
        share the rendezvous code, and the receiver downloads the file
        after it streams through the relay with AES-256-GCM encryption
        derived from an ECDH key exchange. The server never sees plaintext.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <h3>What exists now</h3>
      <ul class="stack-list">
        <li>End-to-end encryption with ECDH P-256 key exchange and AES-256-GCM</li>
        <li>WebSocket relay for encrypted chunk streaming</li>
        <li>Browser file send and receive with progress tracking</li>
        <li>Integrity verification via SHA-256 checksum</li>
        <li>Durable session lifecycle events in PostgreSQL</li>
        <li>Operator visibility into active and completed transfers</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Send</h3>
      <p>
        Pick a file, create a session, and share the rendezvous code with your
        receiver. The file is encrypted in your browser before streaming.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="/send">Send a file</a>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Receive</h3>
      <p>
        Enter a rendezvous code to join a session and receive an encrypted
        file. Integrity is verified before the download is available.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="/receive/demo-code">Receive a file</a>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Ops</h3>
      <p>
        Monitor active transfers, session counts, and lifecycle events
        through the operator dashboard.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="/ops">Operator dashboard</a>
    </article>
  </section>
</AppLayout>
